Ad Text:
Leading global legal firm on the lookout for an experienced Financial Analyst to join the business on an initial 12 month contract basis.

Reporting into the team leader of FP&A, you will provide the Regional Managing Partners and the partnership with insightful decision support analytics to enhance effectiveness and profitability of the supported practice groups.

You will report on business plans, results achieved and whether key metrics are being met. You will assist with communication of results within the practice group to the broader firm. 

You will identify business trends including assisting in the preparation of business cases for partner candidates and utilisation to match forecast needs. You will also provide financial advice regarding productivity and efficiency opportunities to enable the practice group to undertake profit improvement opportunities.

In addition you will identify opportunities to design, develop and
leverage Power BI reporting to support multiple priorities across the
region. These will include supporting the delivery of Business
Development Power BI Dashboards, as well as leveraging different
ideas as the business transitions to Power BI reporting. 

Finally you will review operating results and complete variance analysis. You will also complete budgeting and planning activities for the regional practice group, including updated forecasts during the year. You will also assist with preparation of financials to support business cases for secondments and promotions, as well as other functionally led processes such as the annual pricing review and remuneration reviews.

To be considered for this role you will be CA/CPA qualified and have a minimum of 3 years experience in a similar Analytical or business partnering role. You will have previous experience working with a Senior Executive team and identifying profit drivers and improvement opportunities through the analysis of P&L. You will have sound financial modelling skills.

If this sounds like something you would be interested in hit 'Apply' and send through your CV. For more information you can call David Coupe on 0421 708 002.

SAP Technical (Data) Analyst – Local Government | S/4HANA Migration Play a pivotal role in a major transformation.

Join a progressive Local Council delivering a multi-year SAP S/4HANA program. You’ll bridge business and technical teams to drive data quality, enable confident migration, and support a stable, compliant go-live.

Role type: Contract 
Location: Brisbane (Hybrid)
Reports to: Data & Integration Project Manager

What you’ll do:
Partner with business stakeholders to elicit, document, and prioritise functional and technical data quality requirements for S/4HANA migration.
Act as the primary liaison between data owners and technical/data teams, ensuring alignment on data cleansing needs.
Define the scope of data cleansing, ensuring data meets agreed quality standards prior to migration.
Build and maintain data quality dashboards and reports; track progress and outcomes.
Monitor and report on data cleansing KPIs, highlighting risks and areas for improvement.
Coordinate with testing teams to validate load accuracy and alignment to business requirements.
Provide regular status updates to stakeholders and the project team; escalate issues for resolution.
Work with technical teams to validate data migration, transformation, and integrations from external systems.
Review and validate functional designs, configuration specs, and reporting templates.
Identify gaps/risks in proposed solutions; challenge deviations from strategic financial objectives.
Support testing and deployment (UAT, defect triage, cutover planning).
Assist post–go-live stabilisation (incident tracking, reconciliation, audit readiness).
Leverage SAP Activate and business analysis frameworks (e.g., BABOK) where applicable.
What you’ll bring
Proven experience as a Technical Business Analyst focused on data management & data cleansing.
Strong knowledge of SAP (S/4HANA, ECC, FICO, MM), with data migration/integration project experience.
Hands-on experience working with business data owners to resolve data quality issues.
Familiarity with data cleansing tools (e.g., InfoSteward) and techniques (validation, transformation, reconciliation).
Understanding of data governance principles and best practices.
Proficiency in dashboards, reporting, and metrics to track data cleansing outcomes.
Familiarity with compliance reporting and regulatory requirements.
Experience leading stakeholder engagement and design workshops.
Exposure to SAP Fiori analytical apps and KPI tiles.
Excellent communication skills with both technical and non-technical audiences.
Proven success working with virtual and cross-functional teams across multiple workstreams.
Highly developed written communication (documentation, stakeholder reports, executive decks, technical implementation plans).
Desirable

Experience in large-scale financial transformation within Federal/State/Local Government.
Background in multi-release programs involving financial systems and external integrations.
If this sounds like a role for you, apply now! or reach out to Alan Kocjman 07 3291 5401 for more information.

Exciting opportunity to join SA’s iconic RAA 

Full-time, 12-month maximum term opportunity

Join a tight-knit team with a fun, inclusive and supportive culture

At RAA, we’re on a significant transformation journey — and we’re looking for an experienced Manager Value Management Office to help drive disciplined portfolio delivery, value realisation, and support executive decision-making across our transformation programs and projects.

This role plays a critical part in managing RAA’s transformation portfolio by leading portfolio prioritisation, value tracking, benefits management, investment governance, and quarterly business review (QBR) reporting. You’ll work closely with senior stakeholders across Business Units to ensure our investments deliver measurable value and remain aligned to strategy.

What you’ll be doing

Portfolio Management & Governance

Manage quarterly prioritisation, initiative backlog management, investment drawdowns, capacity planning, and dependency tracking.

Monitor portfolio performance against strategic objectives and escalate risks or issues as required.

Benefits Management & Value Tracking

Manage benefits management and value realisation across the transformation portfolio.

Coordinate benefits tracking, quarterly reporting, and post-implementation reviews, ensuring data quality and accessibility.

Quarterly Business Reviews (QBRs)

Lead end-to-end QBR coordination, consolidating inputs into clear, executive-ready portfolio insights.

Track governance decisions and actions to ensure timely follow-through.

Stakeholder Engagement

Build strong relationships across Business Units, Technology, Finance, and delivery teams.

Act as a key point of contact for portfolio processes, governance standards, and executive reporting support.

Reporting & Analysis

Develop portfolio dashboards and reports, providing insights into performance, financials, and benefits delivery.

Conduct analysis to identify trends, risks, and optimisation opportunities, ensuring data integrity.

What you’ll bring

Qualifications

Tertiary qualification in Business, Finance, Strategy, Project Management, or a related field (mandatory).

Portfolio, Program, or Business Analysis certification (e.g. PfMP, PgMP, PMI-PBA) is desirable.

Experience & Skills

5+ years’ experience in portfolio management, program/project management, business analysis, or similar roles.

Experience identifying and tracking the delivery of value through the execution of strategic initiatives.

Proven experience supporting transformation portfolios in complex, matrixed environments.

Strong analytical capability with the ability to turn complex data into meaningful insights.

Experience coordinating cross-functional stakeholders across business and technology domains.

Excellent organisation and time-management skills with the ability to meet tight deadlines.

Strong written and verbal communication skills, including executive-level reporting.

Advanced Excel skills and experience with portfolio tools and BI platforms such as Power BI.

Experience supporting governance forums, investment committees, and executive reporting.

Background in financial services, insurance, or other regulated industries is highly regarded.

About us

We’re proud to be one of South Australia’s most iconic brands, trusted by members for more than 120 years. SA born-and-bred, RAA might be best known for our road service and insurance products, but we’re excited to be continuously diversifying to better help our members and community.

Our goal? To make life better for South Australians. That’s why we’re proud to offer a range of services to our 820,000+ members, including travel, energy, solar and battery, electric vehicle charging, our RAA Rewards program and more. With motoring still a priority, we’re just as passionate as we were in 1903 about road safety, advocating for a safer SA into the future.

We’re also one of the state’s largest employers, with more than 1100 employees working across our local sites at Mile End, RAA Place (CBD) and Adelaide Airport and our many retail and travel shops. With new office spaces in the city and city fringe in the works, and a buzzing people-first culture, we’re proud to be the State’s #1 Employer Brand.

Benefits

We love our people at RAA and believe our employees should be rewarded for being a part of the RAA family. Some of our employee benefits include:

Free RAA premium road service

Access to our RAA Rewards Program  

Generous discounts on all RAA products

Flexible work arrangements

Ongoing Training & Development opportunities and a Study Support Program

Wellbeing facilities and Corporate Health Insurance Plan

How to apply

To be part of something bigger and work for a passionate South Australian organisation with members at heart click ‘Apply’ to submit your application by 9.00am Monday 2nd February 2026.

You'll need to provide evidence of your eligibility to work in Australia and we'll also need you to undertake a police check before you can work with us at RAA.

We are committed to building a workplace that’s diverse and inclusive, where employees are embraced for their unique qualities and valued for their contributions. We believe a diverse and inclusive workplace brings out the best in everyone and helps us to give our members better service. That's why we encourage applications from everyone, including people living with disability, job seekers of all ages, First Nations Peoples, members of the LGBTIQA+ community and people from culturally diverse backgrounds.

We’ve been proudly serving Australian communities since 1914 and have grown to become a top 30-listed company on the ASX with a portfolio of iconic homegrown brands. At the heart of our continued success is over 115,000 team members working across the country, all contributing to bringing our customers smiles. You’ll not only get to see your work make a difference, you’ll be part of a team working together to help Australians eat and live better every day.

About the team

Our Finance team are a vital partner in every aspect of our business, providing commercial insights to drive our success and influence everything we do. With presence in every department, we analyse performance, and deliver actionable insights that shape our strategic decisions.


About the role



Love turning numbers into insights that drive real impact? As our Business Analyst (Finance), you’ll manage end-to-end financial processes for Online Meals, including weekly payment runs, P&L reporting, and variance analysis. You’ll provide accurate, timely insights and guidance to help the team make informed decisions, while ensuring compliance and continuous improvement in reporting and processes.

This role reports to the Senior Finance Manager (Adjacent Ventures) and is based in Melbourne. You’ll work closely with commercial, supply chain, operations, and marketing teams, as well as external auditors and vendors, making every day varied and full of opportunities to add value. Your responsibilities will include but not limited to:



Support month-end close processes.
Coordinate and collate financial budgets, forecasts and business plans.
Ensure forecast accuracy through the inclusion of the latest market and business information.
Develop action plans to deliver insightful analysis and commercial recommendations.
Manage the period end process and advising financial control of necessary accruals and actions required.
Maintain prepayment schedules and asset registers.


About you and your skills




You’re a detail-driven finance professional who loves solving problems and finding smarter ways to work. You thrive in fast-paced environments and know how to balance accuracy with agility. You’re collaborative, curious, and confident using data to tell a story. You’ll also bring:



Studying towards CA/CPA or equivalent. 
Experience managing financial processes, including accounts payable and payment runs. 
Strong background in P&L reporting and variance analysis. 
Skills in data analysis and developing commercial insights. 
Familiarity with ERP systems (Microsoft Business Central preferred). 
Advanced Excel and strong IT skills.
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills.


If you’re ready to make numbers matter and help shape the future of online meals, we’d love to hear from you.

What’s in it for you?

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.
Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hotdeals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.
Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks’. You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.
Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

About the recruitment process

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that is just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We are committed to creating a workplace that is safe and respectful for our team. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. For further information and additional contact details visit the ‘Our Recruitment Process’ section of our careers site or email inclusionrecruitment@coles.com.au

Join DappleOS – Helping Clinics Thrive

At DappleOS, we’re transforming how clinics grow, stay compliant, and deliver exceptional care.

We build healthcare-first, enterprise SaaS software that clinics rely on every day—where trust, quality, and predictability matter. Our platform brings clinical workflows, operational execution, and business performance into one intelligent system designed to help clinics deliver better patient outcomes and run more profitable, scalable businesses.

As DappleOS continues to scale as an enterprise healthcare platform, this role is essential to strengthening product discipline, reducing ambiguity, and ensuring what we ship is dependable and customer-ready.

We’re looking for a Product Lead (Business Analyst) who loves turning complex healthcare workflows into clear requirements, improving product quality, and driving predictable delivery outcomes.

Position Overview

The Product Lead at DappleOS is a senior, hands-on product role focused on delivering high-quality, healthcare-first enterprise SaaS solutions that customers trust. Reporting to the Chief of Product and operating within the Product Team, this role plays a critical part in translating complex clinical, operational, and commercial needs into clear, reliable product outcomes using Agile and Lean practices.

As DappleOS continues to scale as an enterprise healthcare platform, this role is essential to reducing ambiguity, improving product quality, and ensuring we consistently meet the expectations of our customers. The Product Lead will work closely with Engineering, Customer Success, and Growth teams to define problems clearly, align on outcomes, and deliver solutions that are intuitive, predictable, and dependable.

This is a business-analysis-led product role. The Product Lead is accountable for clarity, quality, and business impact across the full product lifecycle, including ensuring robust User Acceptance Testing (UAT) is completed prior to every release.

Key Responsibilities
Product Discovery & Business Analysis

Work in close partnership with the Chief of Product to define, refine, and evolve the product roadmap in alignment with company strategy and customer needs

Define product requirements and communicate them clearly and effectively to all stakeholders

Partner with Customer Success and Growth to synthesise customer feedback, churn signals, and frontline insights into well-defined problem statements

Translate clinical, operational, and business requirements into clear product requirements, user stories, and acceptance criteria

Enterprise SaaS Product Delivery

Lead the end-to-end product lifecycle from discovery through delivery and iteration

Collaborate closely with Engineering to ensure solutions are technically sound, scalable, and aligned with agreed quality standards

Work with the Head of Product Experience to deliver user-focused solutions, ensuring workflows are intuitive, consistent, and appropriate for enterprise healthcare users

Partner with Engineers to explore, validate, and verify solution approaches prior to and during delivery

Plan, coordinate, and execute User Acceptance Testing (UAT) for each release, ensuring delivered functionality meets defined requirements and acceptance criteria before production release

Product Quality & Risk Management

Act as a steward of product quality, ensuring reliability, usability, and predictability are maintained at all times

Identify and communicate product risks, trade-offs, assumptions, and dependencies early and transparently

Participate in incident reviews, post-release retrospectives, and churn analysis to drive continuous improvement

Use data, customer feedback, and operational signals to inform prioritisation and product decisions

Ensure UAT findings, defects, and gaps are addressed or explicitly accepted prior to release

Cross-Functional Leadership & Alignment

Partner with the Chief of Product to ensure roadmap priorities are clearly understood, communicated, and executable across teams

Serve as a connective leader between Product, Engineering, Customer Success, and Growth

Align stakeholders on priorities, scope, and success metrics before delivery begins

Communicate clearly and proactively on product direction, progress, and trade-offs

Support the Chief of Product in evolving product standards, operating rhythms, and quality practices across the Product Team

Key Deliverables
Core Product Deliverables

Clearly articulated product problem statements grounded in customer, clinical, and business insight 

High-quality product requirements, user stories, and acceptance criteria that remove ambiguity for Engineering 

Consistent, intuitive, user-focused workflows aligned with enterprise healthcare expectations

Quality & Risk Deliverables

Completed and documented User Acceptance Testing (UAT) for every release, aligned to agreed acceptance criteria

Formal UAT sign-off prior to production release, including documented risks or known limitations

Measurable reduction in product quality-related incidents, regressions, and customer-reported defects

Explicit documentation of product risks, assumptions, dependencies, and tradeoffs for major initiatives

Actionable outcomes from incident reviews, retrospectives, and churn analysis translated into product improvements

Demonstrable improvements in reliability, usability, and predictability within assigned product domains

Delivery & Execution Deliverables

Predictable delivery plans with clearly defined scope, priorities, and success metrics

Strong alignment with Engineering on feasibility, sequencing, and technical constraints

On-time, well-communicated releases with minimal surprise to internal teams and customers

Cross-Functional & Business Deliverables

Clear alignment with Customer Success and Growth on customer needs, expectations, and value delivery

Product inputs that support sales enablement, customer onboarding, and retention efforts

Transparent, proactive communication to stakeholders on progress, outcomes, and tradeoffs

Strategic & Team Contribution

Contributions to evolving product standards, quality practices, and operating rhythms within the Product Team

Reduced rework and increased clarity across teams through stronger upfront problem definition

A trusted partnership with the Chief of Product and senior stakeholders

Roadmap & Planning Deliverables

Partner with the Chief of Product to define, maintain, and communicate a clear, prioritised product roadmap aligned to company strategy and customer needs

Break down roadmap initiatives into well-defined product requirements, delivery milestones, and success metrics

Ensure roadmap items are sufficiently shaped, validated, and UAT-ready before entering delivery to reduce execution risk

Maintain clear traceability from strategic roadmap themes to delivered product outcomes

Continuously refine roadmap priorities based on customer feedback, quality signals, business impact, and delivery learnings

Skills & Experience
Required

5+ years of experience in Product Management, Product Lead, or Business Analyst roles within SaaS environments

Demonstrated experience delivering enterprise SaaS products with complex workflows

Strong background in business analysis, requirements definition, and stakeholder alignment

Experience planning and executing User Acceptance Testing (UAT) in collaboration with engineering and business stakeholders

Excellent written and verbal communication skills

Proven ability to bring structure and clarity to ambiguous problem spaces

Experience working closely with Customer Success and Growth teams in enterprise contexts

Strong analytical skills and comfort using data to guide decisions

Bonus

Experience working in healthcare, cosmetic, or other regulated or trust-sensitive industries

Familiarity with scaling product practices beyond early-stage startup environments

Why You’ll Love Working at DappleOS

You’ll work on a healthcare-first platform that clinics rely on every day

You’ll help raise the bar on product quality, predictability, and customer trust as DappleOS scales

You’ll have real ownership shaping how roadmap initiatives become clear requirements and reliable releases

You’ll partner closely with Engineering, Customer Success, and Growth in a highly collaborative environment

You’ll work directly with the Chief of Product and contribute to how DappleOS matures its product operating model

How to Apply

Send your CV and a cover letter explaining:

Why DappleOS is interesting to you

A product or SaaS delivery challenge you’ve solved (and how you approached it)

Your experience turning ambiguity into clear requirements and outcomes

Apply via Seek or email careers@dapple.clinic.

Our client, Department of Education, are currently seeking a Senior Business Analyst for an initial 2 year contract.

The initial project assignment is to support the Queensland Representative School Sports Digital Platform, and will provide a high level of specialist business analysis activities to the Information and Technologies Branch, however the resource model structure undertaken within I&TB encourages a more flexible way of working and during your contract period you may find yourself working on one or more initiatives in conjunction with/or in place of the initial assignment.

The Senior Business Analyst will be responsible for:

Proactively manage key stakeholder relationships, and lead and conduct business/technical workshops and meetings as required to define requirements, business processes, and ensure improved outcomes.
Obtain formal agreement from stakeholders on the scope of requirements (including translating them to features, epics and user stories and associated acceptance criteria).
Where required, initiate communications between stakeholders, acting as a single point of contact for defined groups and facilitating open communication and discussion between stakeholders.
Take responsibility for investigative work to determine business, and specify effective business processes, through improvements in information systems, information management, practices, procedures, and organisation change.
Take ownership of solution design and work with various stakeholders to finalise a compatible design based on industry best practices.
Identify and assist the development of remediation plans to resolve any inconsistent or unclear business practices which could affect the success of the project.
Take responsibility for ensuring traceability is mapped and agreed for all business benefits through to system requirements.
Contribute to organisational change through recommended improvements to existing business processes, practices, procedures and information systems.
Provide a high level of expertise in establishing and documenting ICT business and system requirements through a range of structured research and analysis techniques including, but not limited to facilitated stakeholder workshops, surveys, client meetings and industry reference reviews.
Apply and utilise business modelling methods to ensure results oriented deliverables in a way that can be recreated and used as a corporate knowledge resource available to project level initiatives and executive decision making.
Actively participate in the management of client expectations in a limited resource development environment with competing priorities
Take ownership of development cycles, liaise with vendor’s development team, and ensure quality and timely delivery of agreed outcomes.
Skills and experience required;

Minimum of 5 years’ experience in a Senior Business Analyst role.
Ability to rapidly gain an understanding of business needs and translate business needs into updated process maps and user stories.
Ability to work effectively with little supervision and as part of a team in the design, preparation and delivery of solutions to clients.
Prior experience and knowledge of core ICT infrastructure services such as network and data protection; OR Software as a Services (SaaS) environments; OR Dynamics 365 implementations; OR IT Service Management
Demonstrated well-developed communication, interpersonal and negotiation skills, including the demonstrated experience in conducting workshops, maintaining positive relationships with stakeholders, ICT Operators and other service providers.
Demonstrated experience in identifying and validating multiple requirement types such as Business, systems, configuration and concept and experience modelling business processes using Business Process Modelling Notation (BPMN). 
Demonstrated ability to analyse business cases, which define potential benefits, options for achieving these benefits through development of new or change processes and associated business risk
Demonstrated experience and practical understanding of Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC) and PRINCE2 Project Management methodologies. (SDLC & PRINCE2 Methodologies)
To submit your application, in strict confidence, please submit your resume in Word Format using the appropriate link quoting reference No. 248223.  Should you require further information please email kristy.coulter@hudson.com

Your interest will be treated in the strictest of confidence.

Ad Text:
Senior Business Analyst

At Marinus Link, we value our people and their contributions to our shared success. We’re seeking a Senior Business Analyst who thrives in a collaborative and high-performing environment. This is your opportunity to contribute to a nationally significant project by supporting Business Operations and enterprise-wide transformation initiatives and driving continuous improvement.

If you’re motivated by Marinus Link’s purpose to interconnect Australia’s renewable energy for future generations, and thrive on our mission to deliver Marinus Link in a timely, efficient and sustainable way to ensure long-term benefits to communities and consumers, we want to hear from you!

Your Role

As a Senior Business Analyst, you’ll be a key point of contact for the Digital & Process, providing structured business analysis, process optimisation and system implementation support to enable effective business transformation.

You’ll:

Lead the documentation and analysis of current and future state business processes, including gap and change impact analysis
Gather, validate and document business requirements through stakeholder engagement and facilitated workshops
Support system implementation activities, including configuration, testing, vendor liaison and deployment
Provide data analysis, reporting and insights to inform decision-making and continuous improvement initiatives

AEMO at the Heart of Energy 

AEMO is Australia’s independent energy system and market operator and system planner. AEMO’s purpose is to ensure safe, reliable and affordable energy today, and enable the energy transition for the benefit of all Australians.  Australian governments are now committed to a net zero economy for Australia by 2050 and our vision is to enable this. We have the once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to co-design the future of our energy systems, and our core values revolve around character, commitment, and connection. Join us as we contribute to this significant transition in the energy sector.     

About the role 

AEMO’s DER Reform Delivery team in the Operations Transformation & Reform department is responsible for implementing a range of market reforms specifically related to integrating distributed energy resources (DER) and demand side response initiatives into the NEM, including projects arising from the Energy Security Board (ESB) Post 2025 Market Design Final Advice to Energy Ministers and the Consumer Energy Resources (CER) Taskforce.   

You will be responsible for leading the development and delivery of assigned DER projects. This role will, with our stakeholders, lead or support the design, value assessment and delivery of DER and Flexible Demand Reforms. The services could operate in or outside regulatory frameworks.  

What you will be doing 

Collaborate with AEMO colleagues to bring together relevant subject matter expertise as required for the projects. 

Provide leadership, guidance and mentoring to project team members.  

Work closely with project managers, business analysts and other project team members to ensure projects meet agreed milestones and ensure risks and dependencies with system/process requirements are actively managed. 

Identify and maintain cooperative relationships with key stakeholders (e.g. internal stakeholders and delivery partners, regulatory and government agencies, AEMO members and broader industry participants) and pro-actively manage those stakeholder relationships. 

Provide analysis and strategic advice to managers, the Group Manager, and where appropriate, the Executive Leadership Team.   

What you will bring to the role 

Tertiary qualifications in a relevant context to Energy Markets (e.g. Engineering, Mathematics, Economics, Law, Commerce, Finance, Arts).  

Strong experience in the Energy sector, ideally in DER, with an understanding of the physical operation of the energy markets, commercial concepts, and the political, legal and regulatory framework in which the energy industry operates. 

The ability to convey ideas effectively in a non-technical manner. 

Demonstrated capability to lead project teams taking high level market / service designs to practical implementation in operational energy environments. 

Sound experience developing data-driven analytical insight would be highly regarded, including coding in Python and in R.

The Data Engineer architects and implements robust data integration solutions, working with various data sources including operational systems, databases, file geodatabases, APIs, and external data feeds. This position focuses on ETL/ELT processes, data architecture, and ensuring data integrity throughout the data lifecycle.

The Data Engineer is responsible for cataloguing and maintaining the accuracy of the company application and system integration landscape to ensure efficient data flow and data quality for accurate reporting and BI purposes. The role involves data discovery, analysis, and ETL processes to ensure data quality and integrity is maintained from source system to reporting data warehouse.

This position provides leadership around solution architecture and application integration including data management, data warehousing, as well as for the development of a company-wide data platform. The Data Engineer will lead the technical delivery of data platform and BI solutions through the development of data management and integration standards and governance.

The role requires close collaboration with business stakeholders, application owners, vendors, and other technical personnel to deliver fit-for-purpose technical solutions for system integration, data management and warehousing, analytics, and reporting. This is a hands-on solution architect role in system integration and data management.

Key responsibilities include but are not limited to:

Data Pipeline Development & Engineering

Design and build scalable, robust data pipelines to support data ingestion from multiple source systems
Develop and maintain ETL/ELT processes using modern data engineering tools and cloud platforms
Architect efficient data workflows that ensure reliable, automated data movement across systems
Implement data orchestration and scheduling frameworks for batch and real-time data processing
Optimize pipeline performance for large-scale data processing requirements
Design, development, test, and support of standard integration, analytics and reporting artefacts

Data Quality & Governance

Ensure data quality and consistency standards throughout the data lifecycle

Ad Text:
Mid-level and Senior Power BI Consultants – Melbourne & Sydney locations

About Us

At Agile Insights, we are passionate about empowering organisations to transform through the power of Data & AI. We work with global brands and leading organisations to deliver innovative solutions that solve real business challenges. We have a fantastic, long-standing relationship with Microsoft. We are extremely proud to be a Microsoft Solutions Specialist for four competencies including: Data Analytics and AI, Azure and Digital & App Innovation.

The Opportunity

To support delivery to our growing client base, we are looking for a talented and enthusiastic Senior Consultants to join the team. This is an excellent opportunity for someone looking to take the next step in their career as you will be given every opportunity to learn and develop. In the role, you will have opportunities to work with peers to build the best solutions possible on the Microsoft platform. You will be challenged daily to leverage your expertise and will be given opportunities to hone your skills on interesting projects.

While the role is heavily focused on Power BI, skills within Azure or Power Platforms are also highly desirable. Software Engineering experience will be highly regarded also. The roles are located in Melbourne and Sydney and requires office attendance 3 days a week.

Essential Skills, Knowledge and Qualifications for the Successful Candidate Include (the expected level for each skill will vary according to the level – Mid-level or Senior):

Experience in a technical consulting role.

Ability to partner, negotiate and manage expectations with clients.

Develop complex, best practice Power BI reports and dashboards to a high standard.

Highly competent with DAX and Power Query.

Able to model data and build data sets.

Experience with calculation groups and Tabular editor.

Demonstrated experience with Power BI Pagination, Visualisation and Design concepts, as well as Administration Governance and Security.

Experience with the Power BI service including workspaces, apps and user access.

Demonstrated ability to work to a deadline and manage priorities. 

Excellence in communicating and presenting complex information to technical and non-technical stakeholders, both verbally and in written form.

Strong time management skills, able to balance competing priorities and escalate when required.

Ability to work remotely via Microsoft Teams.

Ability to use productivity tools such as Office, Copilot, GitHub, etc.

Aptitude for critical and analytical thinking, as well as the capacity to leverage out-of-the box solutions.

Keen for a fast-paced environment with opportunities to learn, grow, and be exposed to a variety of problems, clients, and technologies.

UI/UX experience/studies desirable (not essential).

Graphic Design experience/studies desirable (not essential).

You may be asked to show us a portfolio of your work.

Advantageous Power Platform and Azure 

Demonstrated experience with Power Apps, Power BI, or Power Automate.
Build Canvas Power Apps and Model-Driven Power Apps.

Design & implement Dataverse databases within the Power Platform.

Build Flows & Robotic Process Automations (RPA) within Power Automate

Build external-facing portals using Power Portals.

Testing work against the requirements and acceptance criteria.

Experience with Azure SQL Databases, virtual machines, Data Factory.

T-SQL experience, developing solutions within SQL databases including views, procedures, creating jobs and execution plan optimisation.

What’s In It for You?

At Agile Insights, we believe in nurturing talent and creating a supportive, flexible, and rewarding workplace. Here’s what you can look forward to:

Wellbeing: Access to hybrid work arrangements, an Employee Assistance Program, and an individualised gym and wellbeing program.

Flexibility: Work from anywhere for up to 6 weeks per year.

Professional Development: Additional paid leave for certifications and exams, with Agile-sponsored training programs for Microsoft and Databricks certifications. Team Engagement: Enjoy regular team meetups, including state-based gatherings and an annual all-company event. Equipment & Hardware: Receive an allowance for your home office setup and a 2-year equipment incentive. Salary Packaging: Access novated leasing services for tax-effective car purchases. Learning Resources: Expand your skills with access to our digital library and learning platforms. Opportunity to work with some of the best developers in the business including one on one mentoring with senior consultants.

Why Agile Insights?

Work with some of the largest clients and global brands across diverse industries.

Be part of a fast-growing, award-winning team passionate about transforming organisations with Data & AI.

Thrive in a friendly start-up culture that values innovation, collaboration, and work-life balance.

Ready to Lead with Us?

If you’re passionate about analytics, consulting, and community engagement, we’d love to hear from you.

Apply now to join Agile Insights and take your career to the next level!

About Us

From humble beginnings in 2011, Evolution Mining is now a leading gold producer, operating six mines across Australia and Canada. Enacting our vision to be inspired people creating a premier global gold company, we are indeed a bold team with a bright future. Our operational diversity offers our employees access to many experiences and career opportunities within the one company. So, whether you choose to work at one of our underground or open pit operations, explore for our future as part of our Discovery team, or join our Group Office, we know you'll have a bright future with us.

At our Group Office

Working in our Group Office, you have a front row seat to our vision and are a part of the bold, inspired teams who are engineering its success. We're an agile, entrepreneurial company and we value smart people and creative thinking. When you work with us, you'll always have the opportunity to progress from where you started. Based in the Brisbane CBD, our people work with teams located across Australia and Canada which makes for interesting work and countless ways to learn and grow.

Your Benefits

At Evolution, we support, develop and reward everyone who chooses to be a part of our bright future. Your benefits include relocation support assistance, novated car leasing, life insurance and income protection, short term incentives, referral bonuses, recognition program, study assistance, discounted health insurance and wellness days. 

This role will work a 5/2 roster from the Brisbane office with hybrid options available.

We understand that flexible work means something different to everyone and encourage you to have a conversation about the flexible work options available.

About the Role

This is a rare chance to shape something meaningful from day one. Reporting to the Group Manager Financial Planning and Analysis, you will establish and lead our new economic evaluation function, setting the standard for how we assess major projects and investment decisions across the business.

You will draw on your mining experience, technical depth and commercial judgement to bring structure and confidence to large capital evaluations. Your work will turn complex technical inputs into clear, decision ready financial insights. This role has genuine influence, regular exposure to senior leadership and a clear mandate to build consistency, capability and better ways of working.

A few things you will own:

Creating and governing our economic evaluation framework, including risk adjusted modelling
Leading analysis for Life of Mine planning cycles and major studies
Coaching and uplifting modelling capability across teams, including the Analyst who reports directly to you

This is a role for someone who enjoys clarity, challenge and the satisfaction of helping a company mature its commercial discipline.

About You

You will bring a strong foundation in financial or technical analysis, backed by tertiary qualifications in engineering, finance, economics or a related field. You may have 2 to 6 years experience in modelling, planning, commercial analysis or economic evaluation for a mining house, contractor or consultancy, and you are ready for the next step where your work has visible impact.

You will thrive here if you enjoy:

Learning from experienced modellers
Working with structured templates and clear modelling principles
Seeing how decisions are made at a whole of business level

You are motivated by growth, hands on learning and being part of a function that is being built with purpose.
